<div class="refsect1">
<a name="DeeServer.description"></a><h2>Description</h2>
<p>
<a class="link" href="DeeServer.html" title="DeeServer"><span class="type">DeeServer</span></a> allows you to create private connections (connections which 
are not routed via dbus-daemon). Note that, unlike <a class="link" href="DeePeer.html" title="DeePeer"><span class="type">DeePeer</span></a>, <a class="link" href="DeeServer.html" title="DeeServer"><span class="type">DeeServer</span></a>
will always be swarm leader, and clients connected to it cannot overtake
swarm leadership once the server connection is closed.
</p>
</div>
